<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12144b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12144b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12144b"> 144(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> SP on MacCarthy&apos;s / shoulders</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le roi se faisait suivre par son champion. Saint Patrice imita cet exemple; il eut son champion, son homme fort. Ce fut saint Mac-Carthen, qui devint par la suite &eacute;v&egrave;que de Clogher. Il portait sur ses &eacute;paules le saint devenu vieux, quand les voyages apostoliques offraient quelque difficult&eacute;. <br>[12: The king too was followed by his champion. St. Patrick imitated this example, and also had his champion or strong man. This was St Mac-Carthen, who later on became the Bishop of Clogher. <mark>When the Saint was old, he used to carry him on his shoulders</mark> whenever during the Apostle&apos;s missionary journeys the way became difficult. <small> Riguet, Abb&eacute; <a name="RTSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RTSP"><cite title="source">Saint Patrice</cite></a> (1911) 14</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
